/F1 9.5 Tf
12.5 TL
54 742 Td
(Game Control Analysis Report: GO/STAY vs Fold/Check/Raise) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Date: 2026-05-12) Tj
T*
(Scope: analysis only; no application code was changed.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Executive Summary) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The current codebase does not simply replace GO and STAY with Fold, Check, and Raise) Tj
T*
(  everywhere. It has two separate action-control modes:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    1. 357 mode shows GO, STAY, and FOLD during decision rounds.) Tj
T*
(    2. Standard poker mode shows FOLD, CHECK/CALL, and BET/RAISE/ALL-IN during betting rounds.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The most important finding is that FOLD in 357 mode is not a traditional fold. The 357) Tj
T*
(  engine accepts a fold action, but immediately normalizes it to STAY before saving the) Tj
T*
(  decision. In other words, pressing FOLD in 357 should lock the player out of GO for that) Tj
T*
(  3/5/7 decision round, but it does not set the hand player's folded flag and does not remove) Tj
T*
(  the player from the 357 cycle.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What the Buttons Mean Today) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(357 Mode Buttons) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(When the table is in 357 mode and the player can act, the GameControls component renders) Tj
T*
(  three buttons:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    - GO - sends go; the player enters the current 357 round and may compete for the pot.) Tj
T*
(    - STAY - sends stay; the player sits out the current 357 showdown decision.) Tj
T*
(    - FOLD - sends fold, but the engine treats it as STAY for 357.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This rendering is controlled by the mode === '357' branch of GameControls.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Standard Poker Buttons) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(When the table is in standard mode and the player can act, the GameControls component) Tj
T*
(  renders:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    - FOLD - sends fold; the engine marks the player as folded.) Tj
T*
(    - CHECK or CALL amount - shows CHECK if there is nothing to call, otherwise CALL.) Tj
T*
(    - BET or RAISE or ALL-IN - opens the raise panel or sends all-in depending on the) Tj
T*
(      available actions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This rendering is controlled by the mode === 'standard' branch of GameControls.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why GO/STAY and Fold/Check/Raise Appear to Be Replaced) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The behavior is mode-driven:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    - A 357 table intentionally disables traditional betting. The shared 357 config sets) Tj
T*
(      allowCall, allowRaise, and allowTraditionalBetting to false.) Tj
T*
(    - A standard Hold'em table uses traditional poker betting controls.) Tj
T*
(    - The screen chooses which control panel to render from gameSettings.game:) Tj
T*
(  - gameSettings.game === '357' renders the 357 action panel.) Tj
T*
(  - Any non-357 live hand renders the standard hero action section.) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
