54 742 Td
(Therefore, if you see GO/STAY/FOLD, you are in a 357 table/decision round. If you see) Tj
T*
(  FOLD/CHECK/RAISE, you are in a standard poker table/betting round.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Important Finding: 357 FOLD Behavior) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(In the 357 branch of performAction, the engine does this:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    1. Normalizes go, stay, and fold into 357 decisions.) Tj
T*
(    2. Converts FOLD to STAY using const nextDecision = decision === 'FOLD' ? 'STAY' :) Tj
T*
(      decision.) Tj
T*
(    3. Saves that nextDecision into the 357 decision history.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(That means 357 FOLD is currently an alias for STAY. It can look like it works because the) Tj
T*
(  turn advances, but it will later reveal as STAY, not FOLD. This is probably the source of) Tj
T*
(  confusion.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Standard Poker Fold/Check/Raise Behavior) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For standard poker hands, the engine uses true betting logic:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    - Fold sets handPlayer.folded = true and logs that the player folded.) Tj
T*
(    - Check is only allowed when toCall === 0; otherwise it throws Cannot check when facing a) Tj
T*
(      bet.) Tj
T*
(    - Bet is used to open betting when the current bet is zero.) Tj
T*
(    - Raise is used after betting has already started and must beat the current bet and) Tj
T*
(      minimum raise.) Tj
T*
(    - All-in commits the player's remaining chips.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Available standard actions are built per player:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    - fold is always available to the current active player.) Tj
T*
(    - check is available when there is nothing to call.) Tj
T*
(    - call is available when facing a bet.) Tj
T*
(    - bet or raise plus all-in are available when the player still has chips and can increase) Tj
T*
(      the wager.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Gameplay Rules Observed in the Code) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(357 Rules) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    - New 357 cycles deal decision rounds at 3 cards, then 5 cards, then 7 cards.) Tj
T*
(    - Each player secretly chooses GO or STAY for each decision round.) Tj
T*
(    - The current code also accepts FOLD, but records it as STAY.) Tj
T*
(    - If no players GO, there is no payout and the pot carries forward.) Tj
T*
(    - If exactly one player GOes, that player wins the pot and earns one leg.) Tj
T*
(    - If multiple players GO, the best hand wins; losing GO players pay penalty chips to the) Tj
T*
(      winner side and the pot.) Tj
T*
(    - First to 4 legs is displayed as the 357 win target in the UI copy.) Tj
T*
(    - The 357 table config has ante = 1 clip, go-loser penalty to pot = 2 clips, and go-loser) Tj
T*
(      penalty to winner = 2 clips.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Standard Poker Rules) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    - The game defaults to Hold'em in the engine's default settings.) Tj
T*
(    - The hand progresses through normal betting actions: fold, check, call, bet, raise, and) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
