(      all-in.) Tj
T*
(    - Check is valid only when not facing a bet.) Tj
T*
(    - Raise is valid only after betting has started; bet is used to open action.) Tj
T*
(    - The current active player is the only one allowed to act.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How You Can See Each Button Set) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(To see GO/STAY/FOLD) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    1. Create or enter a table whose gameSettings.game is 357.) Tj
T*
(    2. Start a 357 cycle/hand.) Tj
T*
(    3. Wait until it is your decision turn in a decide_3, decide_5, or decide_7 phase.) Tj
T*
(    4. The 357 action panel should show GO, STAY, and FOLD.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Note: the Home screen currently creates a local table with game: '357' and mode: 'HOSTEST'.) Tj
T*
(  In the local transport, that setting is applied and a 357 hand is auto-started.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(To see Fold/Check/Raise) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    1. Create or enter a standard non-357 table, normally Hold'em.) Tj
T*
(    2. Start a hand.) Tj
T*
(    3. Wait until it is your betting turn.) Tj
T*
(    4. If there is no current bet to call, the middle button should show CHECK.) Tj
T*
(    5. If another player has bet, the middle button should show CALL with the call amount.) Tj
T*
(    6. The right button should show BET before betting starts or RAISE after betting starts.) Tj
T*
(      It may show ALL-IN if only all-in is available.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Socket vs Local Transport Note) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(There is a behavioral difference worth checking manually:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    - Local table creation applies input.gameSettings and auto-starts 357 if the input game is) Tj
T*
(      357.) Tj
T*
(    - Socket table creation sends gameSettings from the client, but the current server) Tj
T*
(      player:create_room handler creates a room without applying the payload settings. Since the) Tj
T*
(      engine default is Hold'em, socket-created rooms may default to standard controls unless) Tj
T*
(      settings are updated separately before the hand starts.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This may explain why different testers see different controls depending on local vs socket) Tj
T*
(  transport.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Test Report) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Automated Checks Run) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    - npm run test:357 passed. This validates the current 357 engine flow, including GO/STAY) Tj
T*
(      cycles, solo GO, no GO, reshuffle, tie handling, and leave-mid-round behavior.) Tj
T*
(    - npm run typecheck passed. This validates the TypeScript project after this report-only) Tj
T*
(      change.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Suggested Manual QA Tests) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Test 1: 357 STAY) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    1. Start a local 357 table.) Tj
ET
